Do not say eligible unless&
rules
Wilma should not say
you are eligible
unless the following are confirmed:
For CR-218

exact conviction;
offense class;
not excluded under Title 17-A, Chapter 11;
4 years since full sentence completion;
no later Maine conviction;
no later deferred-disposition dismissal;
no later other-jurisdiction conviction;
no pending charges.
For CR-289
conviction was for former Class E engaging in prostitution under former 853-A;
1 year since full sentence completion;
no disqualifying trafficking/prostitution-related later conviction.
For 2262-B survivor route
user states facts suggesting sex trafficking or sexual exploitation;
user states the conviction was substantially connected to that trafficking/exploitation;
manual/legal review is triggered because this is trauma-sensitive and evidence-specific.
For juvenile
offense class/type confirmed;
discharge date confirmed;
later adjudications/convictions checked;
pending juvenile/adult proceedings checked.
